OL,6,F"A significant number of women and
OL,7,Fgirls who showed remarkable courage to
OL,8,Fspeak up at that time also did not get
OL,9,Fthe justice and support they needed
OL,10,Fand deserved from Strathclyde Police."
OL,12,FAfter the court case, lawyers speaking
OL,13,Fon behalf of Miss Caldwell's mother
OL,14,Fsaid Police Scotland had "blood on
OL,15,Ftheir hands".
OL,17,FMiss Caldwell vanished days after
OL,18,Ftelling her mother Margaret about her
OL,19,Fhopes to overcome a heroin addiction,
OL,20,Fwhich she funded with sex work in
OL,21,FGlasgow.
